WEBVTT

00:05:27.074 --> 00:05:30.147
and journalists tend to be
graduates of humanities departments --

00:05:30.171 --> 00:05:31.713
there is a narrative of decline.

00:05:31.737 --> 00:05:33.777
It's been going on since the 19th century,

00:05:33.801 --> 00:05:38.799
with gloomy philosophers
like Nietzsche and Schopenhauer

00:05:38.823 --> 00:05:40.113
and Heidegger and Sartre,

00:05:40.137 --> 00:05:42.752
and then the postmodernists
and critical theorists.

00:05:42.776 --> 00:05:46.661
That's kind of the culture that you get
steeped in nowadays in a university,

00:05:46.685 --> 00:05:49.060
and that's what journalists come from.

00:05:49.599 --> 00:05:53.506
Combine that with a narrative
that journalists tell themselves

00:05:53.530 --> 00:05:57.641
that in the past, journalism
was too complicit with power --

00:05:57.665 --> 00:06:00.582
you know, Franklin Roosevelt
was never shown in a wheelchair,